Here, we see that applying a coordinate-descent method can be much more efficient than an FG method if Mj << Mσ. This can happen, for example, when the number of variables p is much larger than the number of examples n. Further, it is possible for coordinate descent to be faster than the AFG method if the difference between Mσ and Mj is sufficiently large.
